<br>
I never thought it worked, unless the other guild had the kindness to realize by proceeding with their own plans, they would be disrupting the plans of others.  My own guild practices a policy much like this: If we arrive to where we *thought* we were going to be doing something, and another guild/groups is there, we JUST LEAVE and let them have it.  We can find something else to do, and never wanted to impinge upon other's enjoyment of the game.  <br>
<br>
I am willing to admit I thought other guilds and players followed a similar code: that is what I thought FIF meant.  I've already said that: I was mistaken.  About a great many things, evidently.<br>
<br>
Thormir, Go play, there is nothing keeping you here besides yourself.<br>
<br>
Esbat<br>
I understand now.<br>
